frameDefinitions: An  Agent or non-human Cause causes an Item to change its physical size.
The words in this frame describe the 'fictive' motion of a stationary Road.
An Item changes its physical size.
These are words describing situations in which a Perpetrator wrongs a Victim by taking something (Goods) from them.
An individual or group (Practitioner) or a part of their work life (Work) is defined professionally by the Activity that they typically engage in.
An Entity has existed for a length of time, the Age.

listRoleDefinitions: With some words in this frame, an <fen>Agent</fen> who causes the change in size of the <fen>Item</fen> may be present. The <fen>Agent</fen> typically occurs as the External Argument of a verb.
The <fen>Item</fen> is frequently the External Argument of verbs or the NP Object if an <fen>Agent</fen> is expressed.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is a non-human entity which brings about the change in size.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Item</fen> to expand.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> cause the expansion of the <fen>Item</fen>.

Any expression which implies a definite starting-point of the <fen>Road</fen>. In prepositional phrases, the prepositional object expresses the starting point of motion. In particles, the starting point of motion is understood from context.
The trajectory that would be followed by one moving on the <fen>Road</fen>.
Any expression which tells where the fictive mover travelling along a <fen>Road</fen> would end up.

A physical path that a virtual moving entity can be imagined to travel along.
<fex name='Road'>The bike trail</fex> <t>zigzagged</t> through the woods.
This frame element is used for expressions which describe a general area in which motion takes place when the motion is understood to be irregular and not to consist of a single linear path.
The configuration formed by the entire <fen>Path</fen> along the <fen>Road</fen>.
The direction in which a 'fictive' mover would travel along a <fen>Road</fen>.

The time when the fictive motion takes place.  This may describe the time when the <fen>Road</fen> or a particular piece of the <fen>Road</fen> existed, or it may implicitly describe the time when an actual motion event occurred on the <fen>Road</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the motion (which is specified by a <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen>) is located.
This role identifies the <fen>Item</fen> whose size changes.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the expansion occurs.
The <fen>Perpetrator</fen> is the person (or other agent) that takes the <fen>Goods</fen> away by force or threats.
The <fen>Victim</fen> is the person (or other sentient being or group) that owns the <fen>Goods</fen> before they are taken away by the <fen>Perpetrator</fen>.
Source is the initial location of the goods, before they change location.
The <fen>Time</fen> indicates when the Robbery occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the Robbery occurs.
An activity that defines a group of people in their professional capacity.
The individual, group, or organization  that engages in the <fen>Activity</fen> as part of their profession.
A physical or abstract entity that is characteristically associated with the <fen>Activity</fen>.
A phase of a <fen>Practitioner</fen>'s career that is spent engaged in an <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Practitioner</fen> engages in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Practitioner</fen> engages in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular age is under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is a function of the amount of time that the <fen>Entity</fen> has existed.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Entity</fen>'s age.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Age</fen> from the norm.
The Frame Element <fen>Expressor</fen> marks expressions that indicate a body part, gesture or other expression of the <fen>Entity</fen> that reflect its age.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is at a particular <fen>Age</fen>.
